 Jefferys Bay - The Kouga Local Municipality has invited residents and stakeholders to submit comments on the municipality's draft Integrated Development Plan (IDP) and budget for the 2020/21 financial year. Due to the Covid-19 ban on gatherings, community consultation meetings could not be held. Instead, Kouga Executive Mayor Horatio Hendricks presented the draft documents at a media briefing this morning. Residents are invited to view the media presentation here. Input on the IDP can be emailed to IDP Manager Colleen Dreyer at cdreyer@kouga.gov.za while input on the budget can be emailed to Budget & Treasury Manager Shukree Abrahams at sabrahams@kouga.gov.za. The closing date for submissions is 13:00 on 16 June 2020. The following presentations can be viewed: * Speaker Hattingh Bornman: Covid-19's impact on the public participation process * Mayor Horatio Hendricks: Opening remarks on the public presentation of the draft IDP/budget  * IDP Manager Colleen Dreyer: Draft IDP 2020/21  * CFO Riaaz Lorgat: Draft Budget 2020/21 * The full draft IDP/Budget presentation Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 